	Factorial function
	
	Function definition *
		1. Function type	-	compulsory
		2. Function name	-	compulsory
		3. List of parameters/arguments	-	compulsory
		4. Local variable declaration	-	optional
		5. Function statement	-	compulsory
		6. Return statement	-	optional
	Function declaration/prototype
	Function call
	
	
	* First three function definition elements are collectively
	  known as function header and the rest constitute function body.
	  
	  
	  Datatypes:
	  	- primitive/primary/built-in
	  		int, char, float, double, void
	  	- derived data type
	  		array, function, pointer
	  	- user-defined
	  		struct, union, enum, typedef
